    <div class="page">
        <h2 id="section_1"><span>1</span>Purpose</h2>
        <p>The purpose of the Source Code Review Plan for {{metadata.buildParameter.configItem}} is to guide the activities to be performed during the Coding Review process. The review of source code is performed to verify that the code was developed in accordance to pre-defined Coding Standards and verified against the Software Design. In case of an OpenDevStack (<em>BI-IT-DEVSTACK</em>) component this review is done by SonarQube, automated.</p>
        <p>A Source Code Review Report is developed upon the conclusion of the review process to document the results of the review and indicate the suitability of the code for release to development testing.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="page">
        <h2 id="section_2"><span>2</span>Scope</h2>
        <p>The scope of the automated review, performed by SonarQube, during the build process, is all modules listed below, based on defined quality rule sets (Quality Profiles). The installation of SonarQube is part of OpenDevStack (<em>BI-IT-DEVSTACK</em>) and hence qualified.</p>
        <p>{{{data.sections.sec2.content}}}</p>
    </div>

    <div class="page">
        <h2 id="section_3"><span>3</span>Roles and Responsibilities</h2>
        <p><em>N/A</em>. The review is automated. In case the review passes based on quality gates the pipeline will continue, otherwise it will fail and stop further processes.</p>
        <p>{{{data.sections.sec3.content}}}</p>
    </div>

