        <p>The final list of packages that are scanned and reviewed, is version controlled in the Component's <em>GIT</em> repository, and called <em>sonar-project.properties</em>. Exclusions are mentioned in the property <em>sonar.exclusions</em>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="page">
        <h2 id="section_6"><span>6</span>Applied Coding Standards</h2>
        <p>The rules and guidelines are stored in Sonarqube. Using the server's URL and adding <em>/coding_rules</em> they can be found. These profiles are version controlled, and provide the ability to view any changes that happened (e.g. disabled rules).</p>
        <p>The SCR contains a reference to the activated quality profile which can be reached through: Sonarqube's URL, appending <em>/coding_rules?activation=true&qprofile=</em><b>quality profile link from report</b>.
        <p>{{{data.sections.sec6.content}}}</p>
